race.description: Move To Strike Thoroughbred Club Stakes (G3)
race.comment: Big money on offer for these fillies, and if MY GLADIOLA (1) is able to hold her form, she should be winning. She's been excellent against the top colts, beating home Tentyris two back (with favours) in the G2 Danehill before trying hard behind that horse in the G1 Coolmore when beating home the likes of Beiwacht and Beadman. She's very well suited at the set weights, she'll just need a split from the inside gate. If she's over the top, INKARUNA (2) can run very well on the quick backup from the G3 Red Roses on Oaks Day. She ran well behind stablemate Point Barrow there and that form should hold up. TUPAKARA (4) is interesting off a let up. She was enormous behind Apocalyptic over this trip first up which has her in the mix. TEINE AULELEI (9) is back in trip but going very well.
